    <p>Review velocity — the rate at which new reviews accumulate — is a ranking signal Google reads as a sign of business health and community trust. After every completed job, in every city the company serves, there should be a systematic follow-up requesting a review. Not a mass email to a list — a triggered, timed follow-up sent when customer satisfaction is highest, typically the day the job is confirmed complete.</p>

