    <p><strong>For emergency plumbing searches, the top three map pack positions in Bay Area cities typically have between 50 and 200 reviews.</strong> The review gap for most plumbing contractors not in the pack is primarily a velocity problem — they are not converting completed jobs into reviews at a rate that keeps them competitive. A plumber who completes eight jobs per day and gets zero reviews that week is falling further behind the competitor who does five jobs and converts one review from each.</p>

