    <p>The review velocity target in San Jose is higher than in smaller Bay Area markets. Three to four new reviews per month is the minimum to remain competitive with the current top-three positions. Five to six per month is the velocity that produces upward movement within the pack. Reaching 100 reviews is the first major milestone for map pack stability in San Jose — below that count, the position is vulnerable to any competitor who accelerates their review program.</p>

