    <p>The internal linking structure connects project-type pages to city pages bidirectionally, and blog content that answers homeowner research questions links to the relevant service pages. A post about "drought-tolerant plants for Bay Area front yards" links to the drought-tolerant landscaping service page. A post about "cost of backyard patio in San Jose" links to the hardscape city page for San Jose. Every piece of content is part of the authority architecture, not a standalone asset. The <a href="/keyword-research-for-contractors/">keyword research for contractors</a> process maps which landscaping project-type terms have accessible competition in each target Bay Area city.</p>

